FBIS3-25553 "drafr036_e_94007" FBIS-AFR-94-036 Document Type:Daily Report 23 Feb 1994 WEST AFRICA Niger President Appeals for Debate on Tuareg Proposals LD1902203394 Paris Radio France International in French 1830 GMT 19 Feb 94 LD1902203394 Paris Radio France International Language: French Article Type:BFN [Text] The Niger authorities and the Tuareg rebel leaders are due to meet in Paris at the end of next month to engage in a new round of political negotiations. In the run-up to this meeting, the Coordination of the Armed Resistance, which groups together four Tuareg movements [Front for the Liberation of Tamoust, Liberation Front of Air and Azaouak, Revolutionary Army for the Liberation of North Niger, and Popular Front for the Liberation of the Sahara] has handed a list of its demands to Niger President Mahamane Ousmane. On receiving these demands, the president asked his fellow citizens to make their opinions known. Mahamane Ousmane: [Begin Ousmane recording] In the light of the decisive step that has been taken, I must say that every coming day and week is essential. Once again, I insist and I call on all the sons and daughters of this country to examine without delay the demands that are revealed and expressed in these documents, and rapidly and diligently to offer their contributions so that, as soon as possible, at the end of March at the latest, we are in a position to enter into negotiations on the contents of these different demands leading to a final peace in our country. [end recording]
